summary: 3x08 Theory
body:
3x08 Theory

So I don’t know if this has been said yet but I’m going to say it anyways because it’s been on my mind all day.

The episode title is “I got your number,” which, for the sake of this theory, I’m going to assume has to do with the Jonah/TJ plot.

So we’re almost positive that the dislike Jonah has for TJ stems from when they were younger. There will be a flashback scene where Asher’s younger brother plays young TJ, and Asher’s mom will play Jonah’s mom. In an instagram photo of Asher’s younger brother on set, they are at a baseball field and he is wearing a baseball uniform, so I think it’s safe to assume that the roots of Jonah’s anger stems from something that happened between the two during a baseball season.

Now comes the significance of the episode title, “I got your number.” From my personal experience having played competitive soccer for many years, I know that the kids on the team get to pick their jersey numbers more often than not. I always picked number 15 because that was my uncle’s number when he played soccer, and he was a family member that I looked up to as a role model. Then I got to thinking, with Jonah’s mom being in the scene, perhaps this same concept applied to Jonah?

Maybe one of his family members used to play baseball, and Jonah wanted to have the same jersey number as them. Maybe this family member is no longer alive, and Jonah wanted to have their number on his jersey in their memory. However, TJ gets the number before Jonah can, hence the episode title.

At this point, there’s two possible reasons why Jonah is still mad at TJ to this day about this thing that happened when they were kids. Considering Jonah isn’t the best at communication…

  1. Jonah told his team before they picked their numbers that he wanted a specific number, but didn’t tell them exactly why. So, being the little asshole that TJ probably was as a kid, he picked the number to piss Jonah off. TJ thought that it was just a harmless joke, since it’s just a number on the back of a jersey, but Jonah was infuriated. However, rather than explain to TJ why he wanted the number (because we know that if TJ had known the real meaning behind the number for Jonah, he undoubtedly would have let him have it), Jonah keeps his feelings concealed and later talks to his mom about the whole thing, where he breaks down.
  2. The team picks their numbers one by one, and TJ is ahead of Jonah. TJ doesn’t care about his number, so he randomly picks one of the available ones, which just so happens to be the one that Jonah wanted. Again, instead of confronting TJ about this, Jonah holds a silent grudge against him — which would make sense, since TJ seemed completely unaware of Jonah’s hate for him.

Anyways, this was long but I definitely think it’s plausible. Let me know what y’all think.
